 SHANGHAI, Nov. 4 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Disneyland and Disneytown resumed operations Wednesday after a temporary closure for COVID-19 control. All cast members and third-party employees returning to work in the resort have completed two nucleic acid tests within 48 hours, with all results negative. All environmental samples collected have also tested negative, according to a statement. The site stopped tourist entry on Sunday evening and was temporarily closed for the purpose of epidemic prevention and control.  People walk into Shanghai Disneyland in east China's Shanghai, Nov. 3, 2021. (Xinhua/Ding Ting)  A tourist poses for a photo at the entrance of Shanghai Disneyland in east China's Shanghai, Nov. 3, 2021. (Xinhua/Ding Ting)  People walk past the entrance of Shanghai Disneyland in east China's Shanghai, Nov. 3, 2021. (Xinhua/Ding Ting)  Disneytown is pictured in east China's Shanghai, Nov. 3, 2021. (Xinhua/Ding Ting) Produced by Xinhua Global Serviceâ– 